        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 24 at 11:21PM CDT until April 25 at 12:00AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
East central Hutchinson County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until midnight CDT.

* At 1120 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles east of
Stinnett, or 13 miles northeast of Borger, moving southeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Two inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

* This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
east central Hutchinson County.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
